RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUSTICE ONCE secured inside position around the first turn and stalked the pace up the backstretch, angled out and launched a two wide bid near the quarter pole, collared COLORFUL NATIVE approaching the furlong marker and finished going away. COLORFUL NATIVE set a pressured pace around the first turn and into the backstretch, edged away and held a clear lead nearing the half mile marker, saved ground around the turn then took on the challenge from JUSTICE ONCE turning for home, dueled in upper stretch then failed to be a match approaching the eighth pole but stayed on for second best. JOHN R raced in the back although never far back from the frontend, was ridden along three to four wide around the far turn, stayed four wide into the lane and cleared a share. ALLEN'S ROCKET tracked the pace two wide up the backstretch, let out a notch and advanced into striking distance with three furlongs left to run, failed to sustain through the far turn and steadily weakened through the lane. JUST JOHNNY pressed the pace up the backstretch, came up empty around the far turn, retreated and continued to tire in the drive.
